Class TwoPlayerLogicStrategy

java.lang.Object
com.tron_master.tron.model.logic_strategy.GameLogic
com.tron_master.tron.model.logic_strategy.TwoPlayerLogicStrategy
public class TwoPlayerLogicStrategy extends GameLogic
Game logic strategy for Two-Player mode. Manages two human players, per-player scoring, boost counts, walls, and state transitions for head-to-head play.

    • tick

      public void tick(Runnable stopCallback)
      Advances the two-player game state for each animation tick. Updates players, checks wall collisions, detects match end, and records the outcome and score.
      Parameters:
      stopCallback - callback to stop the game loop if needed

    • reset
